(90, 1, '2014-06-26 17:32:32', '2014-06-26 17:32:32', '<h3>John M. Krambeer, CEO &amp; Founder</h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. John Krambeer is the Founder and Chief Executive Officer of Camden Capital. As Chair of Camden Capital''s Investment Strategy Committee, he is actively involved in managing client relationships and overseeing the investment management process, including manager selection and review.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Krambeer has extensive experience in providing wealthy families with strategic investment advice, including portfolio design and creation along with oversight of investment partnerships. Mr. Krambeer has spent his career working with both traditional and alternative investment managers, evaluating asset allocation strategies, managing long-term equity portfolios and implementing options strategies for large concentrated stock positions.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Prior to forming Camden Capital, Mr. Krambeer spent 16 years at Merrill Lynch, where he and his wealth management team built the firm’s largest Private Banking and Investment Group. Mr. Krambeer has been featured in several wealth management industry publications for his expertise in the independent investment advisory world and his insight on current market conditions.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Krambeer serves as a Trustee for the Autry National Center and is very active in the community, supporting various philanthropic organizations. He was an inaugural member of the Schwab Institutional Advisory Council for Advisors Turning Independent (ATI) - an elite sounding board for firms transitioning to independence in the ever-changing wealth management industry. Mr. Krambeer received a B.S. in Finance from Woodbury University.</p>\n\n<h3>Gary T. Nicklaus, Partner</h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Gary Nicklaus  is Vice Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Nicklaus Companies ("Nicklaus").  Nicklaus is an innovative global organization that has been investing throughout the world for decades, including spending the last 25+ years transacting business in China.  Mr. Nicklaus is a member of the Board of Directors of companies in numerous sectors including Medical Technology, Cloud Computing, NearShore Technology and Camden Capital.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">From 1991 through 2002 Mr. Nicklaus played golf professionally on both the PGA and European Tours. Mr. Nicklaus is an accomplished golf course designer, with courses throughout the United States and abroad, including Wales, Mexico and Spain.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Nicklaus is Co-Chairman of the Children’s Healthcare Charity, Inc., a non-profit organization and primary beneficiary of the Honda Classic, a premier PGA Tour event. Mr. Nicklaus received a bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, with a Major in Finance, from The Ohio State University.</p>\n\n<h3>Mark H. Udis, Partner</h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Mark Udis joined the firm in 2005 and develops, implements and supports client investment portfolios, while also managing the firm’s operations. Mr. Udis maintains strong relationships with clients, investment managers and Camden’s outside partnerships as he continues in his efforts to establish new family relationships. He is actively involved in portfolio management selection as a member of Camden Capital’s Investment Strategy Committee.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Udis began his career with Lockheed Martin and participated in the company’s esteemed Finance &amp; Leadership Development Program during which he rotated through various advanced technology divisions.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Udis received a B.S. in Finance from Lehigh University. An active member of Theta Xi, he served as both President and Treasurer. Mr. Udis continues to serve the fraternity organization as a member of the Board of Directors and Treasurer of the alumni association.</p>\n\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;">Rich P. Bursek, Partner</h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Rich Bursek is responsible for corporate development and the national expansion of Camden. He leads the discovery and successful integration of professionals who passionately share the firm’s investment philosophy, client-centric approach, corporate values and relentless drive to exceed expectations.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Bursek’s responsibilities also include branding, marketing, public relations and client communications, as well as the ongoing development of the firm’s product and service-delivery platform.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Prior to his arrival at Camden Capital, Mr. Bursek was the Chief Operating Officer of a wealth management and trust business with offices throughout Florida. Mr. Bursek has a 20-year track record of working with leading financial services firms and he has led interactive strategy and marketing teams for Fortune 500 companies. Mr. Bursek graduated Summa Cum Laude with a B.S. in Management from Ball State University.</p>\n\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;">Evans Nettles, J.D., CPA, CGMA, CFO &amp; CCO</h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Evans Nettles joined Camden Capital in 2008 with over 15 years of accounting and finance experience. Mr.Nettles oversees the accounting, financial management and regulatory compliance of the company.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Nettles previously worked as an Internal Revenue Agent with the Department of the Treasury, Internal Revenue Service.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Nettles earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Accounting from Woodbury University and a Juris Doctor degree from Valparaiso University School of Law. He is a Certified Public Accountant and an active member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants (AICPA) and the California Society of CPAs.</p>\n\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;">Monte I. Resnick, Managing Director</h3>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Mr. Monte Resnick is a Managing Director of the firm’s wealth management practice throughout Florida. He is actively involved in portfolio management selection as a member of Camden Capital’s Investment Strategy Committee.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">With a background in behavioral finance and goals-based wealth management, affluent individuals, families and foundations entrust Mr. Resnick to provide thoughtful guidance on all matters pertaining to their investment management strategy.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Prior to joining Camden Capital, Mr. Resnick served as an executive director with JP Morgan where he headed up a wealth management team focused on advising affluent clients and foundations. He previously served as vice president within Neuberger Berman’s private wealth management division. Mr. Resnick began his investment career with Wall Street research firm Sanford Bernstein.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Mr. Resnick serves on numerous local boards and committees. He is currently the Immediate Past President of the Board of Governors for Leadership Palm Beach County. Born in Brooklyn, New York, Mr. Resnick earned a Bachelor of Arts in Business and Psychology from the State University of New York at Albany. He has also earned a designation as a certified Legacy Coach.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;"><span style="color: #5e9c68;">Constantine S. Hatzivassiliou, Managing Director</span></p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Mr. Hatzivassiliou advises affluent individuals, families, and institutions, as well as their respective trusts, estates, foundations and endowments on all wealth management and family office related matters.  He works closely with his clients’ tax and legal professionals.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Prior to joining the Camden Capital, Mr. Hatzivassiliou spent seventeen years in the high net worth investment and banking channels of The Bank of New York Mellon, Bernstein Global Wealth Management and Pacific Mercantile.  Before entering the finance arena, he was a Golf Professional and member of the PGA of America.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Mr. Hatzivassiliou is Foundation Board Member for St. Thomas Aquinas High School in Fort Lauderdale, a Trustee with the Boca Raton Chamber of Commerce and Chairman of The Breakers Men’s Association.  He is an active member of the West Palm 100, the National Order of AHEPA, the Hellenic Development Group and the Breakers and Parkland Golf and Country Clubs. He attended the University of Florida and earned a Bachelor of Arts in Liberal Arts and Social Sciences/Economics from Florida Atlantic University, graduating as a member of the National Honors Scholar Society.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;"><span style="color: #5e9c68;">Jayson J. Brown, Director</span></p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Mr. Jayson J. Brown advises high net-worth individuals and families. He is leading member of Camden Capital’s business development and client relationship team that serves prominent families and individuals predominantly domiciled in Florida.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Prior to joining Camden Capital, Mr. Brown was one of the top investment consultants at TD Ameritrade where he implemented investment solutions for affluent families across the country. His high-service approach led him to be recognized as one of the firm’s top producers three years in a row.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Prior to investment services, Mr. Brown was drafted to play professional baseball for the Anaheim Angels. He received a baseball scholarship at Barry University in Miami, where he earned a B.S. in Finance.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;"><span style="color: #5e9c68;">Amanda Courtney, Client Relations Manager</span></p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Amanda Courtney oversees account administration and maintenance. She works with new and existing clients to service all financial requests and inquiries and coordinates transactions and documentation while maintaining investment records. Amanda acts as the company liaison with custodians, investment managers and other outside agencies. She manages client relationships and helps support all facets of the advisory process and client experience. She is a Personal Financial Planner certified by UCLA.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Courtney has worked in the financial services industry since 2003. She began her career at American Business Bank, a commercial bank specializing in serving the middle market business community of Southern California. Ms. Courtney also has experience in commercial real estate, as she worked closely with the Acquisitions and Dispositions Department of Thomas Properties Group, a full service real estate operating company and institutional investment manager.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Courtney earned her B.A. in History from The Catholic University of America in Washington, D.C.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;"><span style="color: #5e9c68;">Michelle R. Lutein, Client Relations Manager</span></p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Michelle Lutein oversees account administration and maintenance for our Florida office. She works with new and existing clients to service all financial requests and inquiries and coordinates transactions and documentation while maintaining investment records. Michelle acts as the company liaison with custodians, investment managers and other outside agencies. She manages client relationships and helps support all facets of the advisory process and client experience.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Lutein has great pride in providing an elite level of service to each of our team’s relationships through her own seasoned experience and through the resources afforded to our team by Camden Capital and its strategic partners.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Lutein has worked in the financial services industry since 1999. Her diverse experience with domestic and international high net worth individuals has been built through her tenure at firms such as Merrill Lynch, Neuberger Berman and J.P. Morgan.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Michelle attended Emory University and graduated with a major in Psychology and a minor in Spanish. Michelle is fluent in Spanish and is in the process of learning Portuguese.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;"><span style="color: #5e9c68;">Natalie M. Trociuk, Client Relations Associate</span></p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Natalie Trociuk serves as a Client Relations Associate for Camden Capital. She supports clients in their financial transactions, provides them with financial information regarding their accounts, and assists in their day-to-day inquiries and requests.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Prior to joining Camden Capital, Natalie worked in the educational services industry, where she guided students through the college application process and subsequently assisted schools within the Los Angeles Unified School District to incorporate educational software into their curriculum.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Trociuk received a Bachelor of Business Administration with a concentration in Marketing, as well as a minor in Russian Studies, from the University of Notre Dame. In addition to her academic studies, she was involved in the Undergraduate Women in Business Club, serving as an officer for 3 years, and worked for the university’s football recruiting office.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;"><span style="color: #5e9c68;">Devon M. Galindo, Client Relations Associate</span></p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Devon Galindo serves as a Client Relations Associate for Camden Capital. She works with new and existing clients in their documentation and financial transactions, assisting them in their day-to-day inquiries and requests. She acts as a liaison with custodians, investment managers and other outside agencies. She manages client relationships and helps support all facets of the advisory process and client experience.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Prior to joining Camden Capital, Ms. Galindo was a Senior Analyst at KLS Professional Advisors Group, a multi-billion dollar wealth management firm focused on investment management, financial decision making and estate, tax, insurance and retirement planning for high net worth individuals and families.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Galindo graduated Summa Cum Laude from Loyola Marymount University, where she received a Bachelor of Business Administration with double majors in Marketing and Entrepreneurship &amp; Management. She remains involved in the Loyola Marymount University Alumni Association and the Delta Sigma Pi Alumni Association. Ms. Galindo will receive a Certificate in Taxation from UCLA in 2014.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;"><span style="color: #5e9c68;">Kristy Nguyen, CFP and </span><span style="color: #5e9c68;">Research Associate</span></p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Ms. Kristy Nguyen is a Financial Planner specializing in strategic tax, retirement and estate planning for clients and their respective trusts and foundations. She oversees all financial plans and is actively involved in investment analysis as a member of Camden Capital’s Investment Committee. Ms. Nguyen also monitors the allocation of the investments and conducts ongoing evaluation of investment selection. With a concentration in tax and investment from UCLA, she designs integrated tax and wealth management strategies with a holistic approach and a strong commitment to long-term client relationships.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Prior to Camden Capital, Ms. Nguyen began her career at Wells Fargo where she strategized optimal investment plans, and later expanded her skills in technical analysis. She managed and developed financial models that included asset allocation, portfolio performance and cash flow analysis.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">As a Certified Financial Planner professional and a Level II CFA candidate, she adheres to the highest ethical and professional standards. Ms. Nguyen is also a member of the CFA Institute.</p>\n<span style="color: #5e9c68;">Matthew L. Schulz, Associate</span>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Mr. Matthew Schulz assists in the development and maintenance of managing client investment portfolios, in addition to handling client performance reporting.  Prior to joining the Camden team, Mr. Schulz worked for a specialty finance company located in Costa Mesa, California, where he focused on structuring debt financing for early stage companies.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Mr. Matthew Schulz graduated from Indiana University with a B.S. in Finance and Minor in East Asian Languages and Cultures.</p>\n<p class="font_7" style="color: #7f7f7f;"><span style="color: #5e9c68;">Bryce W. Horner, Associate</span></p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">Mr. Bryce Horner conducts financial market research and assists in implementing investment solutions, in addition to monitoring and reporting on investment allocations of client accounts. Prior to joining Camden Capital, Mr. Horner analyzed wealth management strategies and performed securities research for a boutique investment advisory firm in Tucson, Arizona.</p>\n<p class="font_8" style="color: #7f7f7f;">He graduated from the University of Arizona with a B.S. in both Finance and Business Economics.</p>', 'Leadership', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-06-26 17:32:32', '2014-06-26 17:32:32', '', 15, 'http://192.168.1.86/camdencapital/15-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
